On the one-year anniversary of Hurricane Sandy, President Obama released a statement acknowledging the devastation caused by the storm and paying tribute to those who lost their lives. He also highlighted the strength and resilience of the American people, citing examples of heroism and community support. The President emphasized that there is still work to be done in terms of rebuilding homes and businesses, but assured that the federal government will continue to support the affected communities. He mentioned the billions of dollars in assistance provided to individuals and small businesses, as well as efforts to cut through red tape and bureaucracy. The President also emphasized the commitment to long-term rebuilding and the progress made in restoring roads, bridges, hospitals, and businesses. He concluded by reaffirming the American value of taking care of one's own and promising to stand with those affected every step of the way.